Author: ekwater
Text: i'm in a really similar situation to you- I even eat a bit more than that! never passed out, never restrict super low, but i am obsessed with calories and agonize about food, feel guilty about eating certain foods... it takes up a disproportionate amount of my brain space.   &#x200B;  but i don't think I have body dysmorphia- i know/can see I'm skinny + even a bit too skinny.  i've started talking to a therapist and so far i am being taken seriously/they care

Author: MissNietzsche
Text: You should be honest really. It's the best way for him to truly help you.
